Auerbach Alan H Bought Puma Biotechnology Inc’s Shares


04/29/2015  by OctaStaff 
			in SEC 13G & 13D Filings 












Share with your friendsYour NameYour EmailRecipient EmailEnter a MessageI read this article and found it very interesting, thought it might be interesting for you. The article is called Auerbach Alan H Bought Puma Biotechnology Inc’s Shares and is was published by Octafinance.com at http://www.octafinance.com/auerbach-alan-h-bought-puma-biotechnology-incs-shares/33898/.CaptchaSubmitAuerbach Alan H increased Position in Puma Biotechnology Inc (NYSE:PBYI)
Auerbach Alan H has filled a SC 13D/A form regarding Puma Biotechnology, Inc  95.35 -0.50 -0.52%. Per Auerbach Alan H’s filing, the filler reported increased stake in the company by 6.10% to 6,556,249 shares. Auerbach Alan H now owns 18.9% of the Health Care-company. This form was required due to trading activity on April17, 2015.
Puma Biotechnology, Inc Hedge Funds Ownership

Latest SEC filings show 180 hedge funds and institutional investors own Puma Biotechnology, Inc. The institutional ownership of the company in Q4 2014 is high, at 84.80% of the shares outstanding. They increased by 623627 the total shares they hold. As of that quarter these institutional investors owned 27067012 shares. A total of 37 funds opened new positions in Puma Biotechnology, Inc and 73 increased their holdings. There were 33 funds that closed their positions and 53 that reduced them.
5 investors have the firm in their Top 10. Some of these are: Adage Capital Partners Gp Llc, Cormorant Asset Management Llc, Ghost Tree Capital Llc, Lamond Capital Partners Llc, Lmr Partners Llp..
 Franklin Street Advisors Inc is the most positive institutional investor on Puma Biotechnology, Inc, with ownership of 19755 shares as of Q4 2014 for 0.71% of the fund’s portfolio. Phill Gross And Robert Atchinson Adage Capital Partners Gp Llc is another positive player owning 5686668 shares of the company or 2.63% of their stocks portfolio. MA Cormorant Asset Management Llc have 6.42% of their stock portfolio invested in the stock for 220000. Further, Ghost Tree Capital Llc disclosed it had purchased a stake worth 2.72% of the fund’s stock portfolio in the company. The CA Lamond Capital Partners Llc was also a notable investor in the firm, owning 55005 shares. Puma Biotechnology, Inc is 6.82% of the fund’s stock portfolio.
Company Profile
Puma Biotechnology, Inc. is a development-stage biopharmaceutical company that acquires and develops innovative products for the treatment of various forms of cancer. The Company focuses on in-licensing drug candidates that are undergoing or have already completed initial clinical testing for the treatment of cancer and then seeks to further develop those drug candidates for commercial use. The Company’s drug candidates include PB272 (neratinib (oral)) for the treatment of advanced breast cancer patients, non-small cell lung cancer patients and patients with HER2 mutation-positive solid tumors; PB272 (neratinib (intravenous)) for the treatment of advanced cancer patients, and PB357.

Form 13D is SEC filing that must be submitted within 10 days, by anyone who acquires beneficial ownership of more than 5% of any publicly traded securities. A filer must promptly update its 13D filing in case of acquisition or disposition of 1% or more of the securities that are the subject of the filing. These filings may be a precursor to hostile takeovers, company breakups, and other “change of control” events.

